Docker networking is the mechanism that allows containers to communicate with each other, the host machine, and external networks. Every container is connected to a network, and Docker provides multiple network drivers depending on the use case.

1. Why Docker Networking?

Without networking, containers would be isolated.

Docker networking enables:

Container ↔ Container communication
Container ↔ Host communication
Container ↔ Internet communication
Communication across multiple Docker hosts

Example:

+---------------- Host ----------------+

        Docker Engine
              |
   -------------------------
   |          |            |
Container1 Container2 Container3
 (Web)      (API)      (Database)

The web container talks to the API container, and the API talks to the database.

