19. Useful Commands
Command	Purpose
docker network ls	List networks
docker network inspect <network>	Show network details
docker network create <name>	Create a network
docker network rm <name>	Remove a network
docker network prune	Remove unused networks
docker network connect <network> <container>	Attach a container
docker network disconnect <network> <container>	Detach a container
docker inspect <container>	Show container networking details
docker exec -it <container> ip addr	Show interfaces inside a container
docker exec -it <container> ip route	Show routing table
docker exec -it <container> ping <container>	Test connectivity
docker exec -it <container> ss -tuln	Show listening ports
docker port <container>	Show published ports
20. End-to-End Example

Step 1: Create a network

docker network create app-net

Step 2: Start a database container

docker run -d \
  --name mysql \
  --network app-net \
  -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=password \
  mysql:8

Step 3: Start an application container

docker run -d \
  --name webapp \
  --network app-net \
  -p 8080:8080 \
  myapp:latest

Step 4: Verify the network

docker network inspect app-net

You should see both mysql and webapp attached to the network.

Step 5: Test connectivity from the application container

docker exec -it webapp ping mysql

The application can connect to the database using the hostname mysql instead of an IP address.
